2085854591.text: "Western analysis of the tumor lysates indicated that, similar to prostate cancer cells in vitro, treatment with simvastatin significantly impaired phosphorylation of Bad (p < 0.01), decreased protein levels of Bcl-2 and Bcl-xL (p < 0.01 and p < 0.001, respectively), increased release of cytochrome C from the mitochondria to cytosol (p < 0.05) as well as increased protein expressions of BimL and BimS, cleaved caspase 9 and cleaved caspase 3 (p < 0.05), compared to saline treated controls."
